From: Steffen Nurpmeso <sdaoden@users.sf.net>
Date: Mon, 12 Jan 2015 20:23:32 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 09/12] mdocmx(7): forgot ^A documentation in less.hlp (Doug
 McIlroy)..

Yes, so he said on TUHS

  Sorry for veering away from Unix history, but this pushed one of the hottest
  of my buttons. Less is the epitome of modern Unix decadence. Besides the
  maddening behavior described above, why, when all screens have a scroll bar,
  should a pager do its own scrolling? But for a quantitative measure of
  decadence, try less --help | wc. It takes excess to a level not dreamed of
  in Pike's classic critique, "cat -v considered harmful".

Clearly mdocmx(7) needs to be documented, too.
---
 less.hlp | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/less.hlp b/less.hlp
index 2a8e3e7..dc73edb 100644
--- a/less.hlp
+++ b/less.hlp
@@ -67,6 +67,8 @@
         Each "find open bracket" command goes backward to the open bracket 
           matching the (_N-th) close bracket in the bottom line.
 
+  ^A_<_t_e_x_t_>             Go to mdocmx(7) anchor <text>.
+
   m_<_l_e_t_t_e_r_>            Mark the current position with <letter>.
   '_<_l_e_t_t_e_r_>            Go to a previously marked position.
   ''                   Go to the previous position.
-- 
